1.text: Sketch the outline of the eye using a pencil.

2.text: Draw the outline of the iris and pupil.

3.text: Use curved lines to create long eyelashes above and below the eye.

4.text: Draw a curved upper eyelid to give the eye depth.

5.text: Sketch a faint outline of the eyebrow.

6.text: Outline areas you'd like to leave light.

7.text: Sketch around the middle ring of the iris.

8.text: Fill in the pupil and darken the outline of the iris.

9.text: Sketch spokes that radiate from the pupil across the highlighted part of the iris.

10.text: Use an eraser or blending stump to lighten the iris.

12.text: Go back and fill in the eyebrow with lots of short hairs.

13.text: Add light shading around the white of the eye.

14.text: Shade the skin around the eye.
